      ],
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "selector",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The selector code for the information you need. You can provide any of the four-character sequences defined in "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coreservices/carbon_core/gestalt_manager#1667886"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "response",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "On input, "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "Gestalt"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " interprets this parameter as an address at which it is to place the result returned by the selector function. "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "Gestalt"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " ignores any information already at this address. "
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "On return, a pointer to the requested information whose format depends on the selector code specified in the selector parameter. Note that the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "Gestalt"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " function returns the response from all selectors in a long word, which occupies 4 bytes. When not all 4 bytes are needed, the significant information appears in the low-order byte or bytes."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A result code. See "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coreservices/carbon_core/gestalt_manager"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The Apple-defined selector codes fall into two categories: environmental selectors, which supply specific environmental information you can use to control the behavior of your application, and informational selectors, which canâ€™t supply information you can use to determine what hardware or software features are available. You can use one of the selector codes defined by Apple or a selector code defined by a third-party product."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Selectors with the suffix "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "Attr"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " return a 32-bit response value in which the individual bits represent specific attributes. The constants listed for these response values represent bit numbers.  "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Special Considerations",
          "anchor": "1677091"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When passed one of the Apple-defined selector codes, the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "Gestalt"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function does not move or purge memory and therefore may be called even at interrupt time. However, selector functions associated with non-Apple selector codes might move or purge memory, and third-party software can alter the Apple-defined selector functions. Therefore, it is safest always to assume that "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "Gestalt"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " could move or purge memory."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Version-Notes",
          "anchor": "1677095"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "ROMVersion"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "  and "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "machineType"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " selectors are not supported in Carbon."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In general, the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "Gestalt"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function returns a different result when called from a Carbon application running in macOS than it returns when called from a Classic application in macOS, because these are different environments. For example, Carbon does not use a ROM, so calling "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "Gestalt"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " from a Carbon application on a beige G3 Macintosh computer and passing the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "ROMVersion"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " selector returns a  different result than Gestalt returns for a Classic application on the same computer."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
